==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[open]]'' + ''[[-er]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈəʊpənə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[device]] that [[open]]s something; specifically a [[tin-opener]]/[[can-opener]], or a [[bottle-opener]].
# (''card games'') The [[player]] who starts the [[betting]].
# (''card games'') (''in plural'' '''openers''') Cards of sufficient [[value]] to enable a player to open the betting.
# (''theatre'') The first [[act]] in a [[variety]] [[show]].
# (''cricket'') A [[batsman]] who normally plays in the first two [[position]]s of an [[innings]].
# (''colloquial'') The first in a series of events, items etc.; the first remark or sentence of a conversation.

